Text.Value: How long d'you think we've got before the goblins come?
I fought for your people at the gate. Show some gratitude.
Speak to me in such a way again, and I will.
Leave m-me alone. I b-beg you.
Please. I've... I've been through enough.
It saw us 'fore we saw it. Jammed its blade through Yul's belly, straight to the other side.
P-p-please.
Please. I've... I've been through enough.
We should be getting drunk, at least. It's no fun waiting for death sober.
Now get away from me!
You've seen other githyanki? Tell me where - or I'll have your head.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Prior to gith chokepoint, otherwise this info is useless to the player so failing this option might have them reload for nothing

Text.Value: P-please. Just leave me alone.
Please. I've... I've been through enough.
OTHER GITHYANKI - WHERE?
I'll t-tell you. Just stay back, all right?
Leave.
Leave me alone, toad, or... or... just leave me alone!
Stand back, toad. I owe you nothing!
My friend's blood not enough? Come to rip me open too?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The tiefling raises his weapon half-heartedly.

Text.Value: And I just... I just ran.
They were on the road to Baldur's Gate, near the mountain p-pass.
Leave m-me alone. I b-beg you.
By Mordai's eyes, another one.

EditorData.NodeContext: Putting on a good front, but slightly afraid. Should still sound confident though.

Text.Value: You did not fight to aid us. You simply craved the taste of blood.

Synopsis: Tiefling is afraid of githyanki - he's seen one gut his friend while they were scouting.
